IMF Board Plans ‘Informal Session’ Today on Strauss-Kahn Arrest

-- B y   S a n d r i n e   R a s t e l l o
-- 
2011-05-15T16:24:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/imf-board-plans-informal-session-today-on-strauss-kahn-arrest.html
The International Monetary Fund
executive board will hold an “informal session” today to
discuss developments regarding Managing Director
 Dominique Strauss-Kahn , who was charged with attempted rape and
a criminal sex act on a maid in a New York hotel, an IMF
spokesman said.  “In line with standard IMF procedures,  John Lipsky , the
First Deputy Managing Director, is Acting Managing Director
while” Strauss-Kahn is away from Washington, IMF spokesman
William Murray said in an e-mailed statement. IMF Deputy
Managing Director Nemat Shafik will attend a meeting of finance
ministers from the euro region in Brussels tomorrow, which
Strauss-Kahn was due to attend, Murray said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  